    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting a collector-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Titanium Silver over Black Nappa leather. This specimen is powered by the legendary S54B32 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure double VANOS system that provides linear power delivery up to its 8,000 RPM redline. This example is equipped with the desirable Getrag 6-speed manual transmission, offering crisp, mechanical shift throws. Crucially, the rear subframe has undergone preventative reinforcement, and the rod bearing service is fully documented, mitigating the two primary concerns for this chassis. The suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications with no signs of bushing fatigue or damper leakage. The exterior retains its original VIN-matched panels with consistent paint meter readings, while the interior shows no bolster wear or delamination of the center console's soft-touch plastics. A mechanically synchronized and aesthetically preserved icon of the M-division's naturally aspirated era.",
